{
  "texts": [
    "It is calculated by summing the normalized distances between an individual and its closest neighbors for each objective.",
    "Individuals with larger crowding distances are preferred during selection, as this helps prevent premature convergence and ensures a more diverse spread of solutions along the Pareto front.",
    "This mechanism enables NSGA-II to explore the solution space more effectively while maintaining diversity.",
    "Reinforcement Learning (RL)RL represents the challenge encountered by an agent required to acquire behavior via trial-and-error interactions within a dynamic environment.",
    "RL has advanced the field of artificial intelligence by enabling agents to learn optimal behaviors through these interactions."
  ]
}